Is there any specific significance to this? 
I have looked into the source code of the pipeline and found that this is an unavoidable behavior, but I have not found any actions that depend on these messages. 
When there are a large number of results, this is a significant waste of resource storage in ETCD.

Thanks @pritidesai for catching this:
This is a current behaviour in Tekton Pipeline:

```
kubectl create -f examples/v1/pipelineruns/pipeline-with-displayname.yaml
kubectl get pr sum-wwmjd(replace with the actual PipelineRun name) -o json | jq .status
```

